Preconditions:
- The input board must be an 8x8 array.
- The board must contain exactly one cell with the value 'R' representing the white rook.
- The board can contain any number of cells with the value 'B' representing white bishops.
- The board can contain any number of cells with the value 'p' representing black pawns.
- The board can contain any number of cells with the value '.' representing empty squares.

Postconditions:
- The method should return an integer representing the number of pawns that the rook is attacking.
- The returned value should be the maximum number of pawns that the rook can capture in any direction (north, east, south, or west).
- If the rook cannot capture any pawns, the method should return 0.